"Kitoh A.","Variability of Indian monsoon-ENSO relationship in a 1000-year MRI-CGCM2.2 simulation",2007,"Natural Hazards","42","2",,"261","272",,,10.1007/s11069-006-9092-z,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-56349152517&partnerID=40&md5=b7a3707d8a08b79fd68559f0a9daaea3","Climate Research Department, Meteorological Research Institute, 1-1 Nagamine, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0052, Japan","Kitoh, A., Climate Research Department, Meteorological Research Institute, 1-1 Nagamine, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0052, Japan","There is a close relationship between interannual variability of the Indian summer monsoon rainfall and the El Niño/Southern Oscillation (ENSO) (drought conditions over India accompany warm ENSO events and vice versa). However, recent observations suggest a weakening of this ENSO-monsoon relationship that may be linked to global warming. We report here an analysis of the ENSO-monsoon relationship within the framework of a 1000-year control simulation of the MRI-coupled general circulation model (GCM), MRI-CGCM2.2. An overall correlation between the June-July-August (JJA) Nino3.4 sea surface temperature and the JJA Indian monsoon rainfall is -0.39, with reasonable circulation characteristics associated with the modeled ENSO. The simulated ENSO-monsoon relationship reveals long-term variations, from -0.71 to +0.07, in moving 31-year windows. This modulation in the ENSO-monsoon relationship is associated with decadal variability of the climate system. © 2007 Springer Science+Business Media, Inc.","Decadal variability; ENSO; ENSO-monsoon relationship; GCM; Global warming; Indian monsoon","annual variation; atmospheric circulation; computer simulation; decadal variation; drought; El Nino-Southern Oscillation; general circulation model; global warming; monsoon; rainfall; sea surface temperature; summer; India",,,,,,"Ashok, K., Guan, Z., Yamagata, T., Impact of the Indian Ocean dipole on the relationship between the Indian monsoon rainfall and ENSO (2001) Geophysical Research Letters, 28 (23), pp. 4499-4502. , DOI 10.1029/2001GL013294; Ashrit, R.G., Rupa Kumar, K., Krishna Kumar, K., ENSO-Monsoon relationship in a greenhouse warming scenario (2001) Geophysical Research Letters, 28 (9), pp. 1727-1730. , DOI 10.1029/2000GL012489; Ashrit, R.G., Douville, H., Kumar, K.R., Response of the Indian monsoon and ENSO-monsoon teleconnection to enhanced greenhouse effect in the CNRM coupled model (2003) Journal of the Meteorological Society of Japan, 81 (4), pp. 779-803. , DOI 10.2151/jmsj.81.779; Ashrit, R.G., Kitoh, A., Yukimoto, S., Transient response of ENSO-monsoon teleconnection in MRI-CGCM2.2 climate change simulations (2005) Journal of the Meteorological Society of Japan, 83 (3), pp. 273-291. , DOI 10.2151/jmsj.83.273; Chang, C.-P., Harr, P., Ju, J., Possible roles of Atlantic circulations on the weakening Indian monsoon rainfall-ENSO relationship (2001) J Climate, 14, pp. 2376-2380. , 10.1175/1520-0442(2001)014<2376:PROACO>2.0.CO;2; Goswami, B.N., The Asian monsoon: Interdecadal variability (2006) The Asian Monsoon, pp. 295-327. , B. Wang (eds). Springer-Praxis Chichester. 10.1007/3-540-37722-0-7; Kawamura, R., Matsuura, T., Iizuka, S., Equatorially symmetric impact of the El Nino-Southern Oscillation on the South Asian summer monsoon system (2003) J Meteor Soc Jpn, 81, pp. 1329-1352. , 10.2151/jmsj.81.1329; Kirtman, B.P., Shukla, J., Influence of the Indian summer monsoon on ENSO (2000) Q J R Meteor Soc, 126, pp. 213-239. , 10.1256/smsqj.56210; Kitoh, A., Effects of mountain uplift on East Asian summer climate investigated by a coupled atmosphere-ocean GCM (2004) J Climate, 17, pp. 783-802. , 10.1175/1520-0442(2004)017<0783:EOMUOE>2.0.CO;2; Kripalani, R.H., Kulkarni, A., Rainfall variability over southeast Asia - Connections with Indian monsoon and ENSO extremes: New perspectives (1997) Int J Climatol, 17, pp. 1155-1168. , 10.1002/(SICI)1097-0088(199709)17:11<1155::AID-JOC188>3.0.CO;2-B; Kumar, K.K., Rajagopalan, B., Cane, M.A., On the weakening relationship between the indian monsoon and ENSO (1999) Science, 284 (5423), pp. 2156-2159. , DOI 10.1126/science.284.5423.2156; Krishnamurthy, V., Goswami, B.N., Indian monsoon-ENSO relationship on interdecadal timescale (2000) J Climate, 13, pp. 579-595. , 10.1175/1520-0442(2000)013<0579:IMEROI>2.0.CO;2; Neelin, J.D., Battisti, D.S., Hirst, A.C., Jin, F.-F., Wakata, Y., Yamagata, T., Zebiak, S.E., ENSO theory (1998) J Geophys Res, 103, p. 14. , 10.1029/97JC03424; Pai, D.S., A possible mechanism for the weakening of El Niño-monsoon relationship during the recent decade (2004) Meteorology and Atmospheric Physics, 86 (3-4), pp. 143-157. , DOI 10.1007/s00703-003-0608-8; Parthasarathy, B., Munot, A.A., Kothawale, D.R., All-India monthly and seasonal rainfall series: 1871-1993 (1994) Theor Appl Climatol, 49, pp. 217-224. , 10.1007/BF00867461; Rajendran, K., Kitoh, A., Yukimoto, S., South and East Asian summer monsoon climate and variation in the MRI coupled model (MRI-CGCM2) (2004) J Climate, 17, pp. 763-782. , 10.1175/1520-0442(2004)017<0763:SAEASM>2.0.CO;2; Rayner, N.A., Folland, C.K., Parker, D.E., Horton, E.B., A new global sea-ice and sea surface temperature (GISST) data set for 1903-1994 for forcing climate models (1995) Hadley Centre Internal Note No. 69, , Met Office, Bracknell, UK; Saji, N.H., Goswami, B.N., Vinayachandran, P.N., Yamagata, T., A dipole mode in the tropical Indian Ocean (1999) Nature, 401, pp. 360-363; Webster, P.J., Magaña, V.O., Palmer, T.N., Shukla, J., Tomas, R.A., Yanai, M., Yasunari, T., Monsoons: Processes, predictability, and the prospects for prediction (1998) J. Geophys. Res, 103, p. 14. , 10.1029/97JC02719; Wu, R., Kirtman, B.P., On the impacts of the Indian summer monsoon on ENSO in a coupled GCM (2003) Quarterly Journal of the Royal Meteorological Society, 129 (595 PART B), pp. 3439-3468. , DOI 10.1256/qj.02.214; Yasunari, T., Impact of Indian monsoon on the coupled atmosphere/ocean system in the tropical P